Date: Thu, 15 May 2014 12:36:03 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] sched: make RT_RUNTIME_SHARE false by default

Even though we've fixed the RCU stalls that get tripped by this
feature, lets disable it by default, since the assumption is that
people using RT will manually architect their system by assigning
tasks to cores directly and similar tuning.  Hence having one
core's rt_runtime shrink to grow anothers can be seen as an element
of non-determinism that most likely is not desired on such a system.

Signed-off-by: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>

diff --git a/kernel/sched/features.h b/kernel/sched/features.h
index 45940519d35a..b7df0ff95716 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/features.h
+++ b/kernel/sched/features.h
@@ -64,7 +64,7 @@ SCHED_FEAT(PREEMPT_LAZY, true)
 #endif
 
 SCHED_FEAT(FORCE_SD_OVERLAP, false)
-SCHED_FEAT(RT_RUNTIME_SHARE, true)
+SCHED_FEAT(RT_RUNTIME_SHARE, false)
 SCHED_FEAT(LB_MIN, false)
 
